➜Lectures about China's Lunar Missions given to kids in Guiyang
http://www.sohu.com/a/439089404_162758	36700
<p><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201218/22178aafd37b422994f975446e50331f.jpeg" /></p>
<p>Photo taken on Dec.17, 2020 shows students learning about Chinese space missions in Guiyang. As China's three-step robotic lunar program is about to be successfully completed, teacher from primary and secondary schools in Nanming district have given classes about China's lunar program, in order to arouse students' interest in aerospace knowledge. (Zho Song/Guangming Picture)</p>
<p><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201218/81eebf0e9a054dc69f71f4e7698c3788.jpeg" /></p>
